<plot>As the Danish architect Lauritz de Thurah in 1748 projected a spire to Our Saviour's Church in Christianshavn he created a piece of architecture which is regarded as a masterpiece of the baroque. But how could a provinsial outpost as Copenhagen create such a marvel? And why did Thurah choose a spiral as a motif?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?239730</url></doc>
